Cool app.  With my DVB-T dongle, I can see signals from 25 MHz to 2200 MHz.  I can actually tune all the way down to DC with the app, but my antenna is not matched for that range.  I assumed that is out of band for my dongle as well.  I really like the waterfall and live spectrum.  User experience is seamless with all the features advertised.    I only gave 4 stars because I feel that there are other features that Mr. (Dr. ?) Marinov could add to make this app truly stellar.       A few ideas of mine: - Live constellation view outside of FM mode.  I would really like to look at BPSK and QPSK constellations that could be generated in ISM bands - Demodulation of other signals such as PSK and FSK.   - Settable integration bandwidth for power readings - Adjustable resolution bandwidth - Markers with deltas so that I could compare power levels of two or more signals (or portions of a signal) in band. - Adjustable power scale and resolution in spectrum and waterfall - Absolute calibrated power in dBm on the spectrum.  That might be pretty hard because of the array of devices that this app can use. - Different color maps and adjustable time resolution for the waterfall
